;Digital Inclusion means promoting diversity
Digitale insluiting beteken bevordering van diversiteit


;For the Internet to fulfill its greatest promise, it must reflect the diversity and experience of all people, everywhere.
As die Internet sy grootste belofte wil vervul, moet dit die diversiteit en ondervinding van alle mense, oral weerspieël.


;As inclusive as the Web can seem, it’s not yet an equal playing field. More than half the world is still without it; emerging economies and marginalized communities are often the last to gain access. Far fewer women are using the Internet than men. And without diversity among its creators, the Web itself will reflect unconscious biases, while personalizing algorithms can reinforce our own.
Hoe inklusief die Web ook mag lyk, is die speelveld nog nie gelyk nie. Meer as helfte van die wêreld het nog nie toegang nie; ontluikende ekonomieë en gemarginaliseerde gemeenskappe kry gewoonlik laaste toegang. Heelwat minder vroue as mans gebruik die Internet. En sonder diversiteit onder sy skeppers, sal die Web onbewuste vooroordele reflekteer, en algoritmes wat verpersoonlik kan ons eies versterk.


;In nine developing countries, women are still nearly 50% less likely to access the Internet than men.
In nege ontwikkelende lande gebruik vroue steeds byna 50% minder waarskynlik die Internet as mans.


;Source: <a href="%(wwwf)s">World Wide Web Foundation</a>, 2015
Bron: <a href="%(wwwf)s">World Wide Web Foundation</a>, 2015


