;Digital Inclusion means supporting universal access to the whole Internet
Digitale insluiting beteken ondersteuning vir universele toegang tot die hele Internet


;We should all have affordable, high-quality, unrestricted access to the whole Web, so the whole world can benefit.
Ons moet almal bekostigbare, hoëgehalte-, onbeperkte toegang hê tot die hele Web sodat die hele wêreld daarby kan baat.


;To participate online, you have to be able to get online. Programs have emerged that offer free or subsidized Internet access, but it is often slow or restricted, creating a ‘poor Internet for poor people.’ At its most extreme, governments worldwide are turning off all or parts of the Internet to serve their own agendas, which can threaten human rights and even the health of the global economy.
Om deel te neem aanlyn, moet mens in staat wees om aanlyn te kom. Programme het na vore gekom wat gratis of gesubsidieerde Internettoegang aanbied, maar dit is dikwels stadig of beperk, en dit skep 'n “arm Internet vir arm mense.” Meer ekstreme gevalle is hoe regerings wêreldwyd Internettoegang of dele daarvan afskakel om hulle eie agendas te dien. Dit kan menseregte asook die gesondheid van die wêreldekonomie bedreig.


